text:
Experts have warned that protests over the death of George Floyd could lead to another wave of COVID-19 infections.

So far, Minneapolis has not seen a dramatic uptick in cases related to the demonstrations, Minnesota's Department of Health told @ABC News. https://t.co/x2jS7xEGBM

name: ABC
text: As of late last week, 4,487 tests conducted across four testing sites specifically for protesters resulted in 62 positive cases of COVID-19, for a positivity rate of 1.4%, according to Minnesota's Department of Health. https://t.co/z4ounnlAdF
